      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios including at least two load levels and two construct configurations.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 configuration (44 mm inter-vertebral body spacer, 5° loading angle) at a single load rate. Although this is the standard regulatory configuration, the absence of additional load levels or construct geometries limits the achieved level to 2. This is the one factor below the required level; risk accepted given regulatory precedent for this configuration."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
