    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for a Medium-risk model. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted on the basis of regulatory precedent: ASTM F1717 specifies a single standardized configuration that is universally applied in 510(k) submissions for spinal fixation systems. All quantitative validation metrics (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%) passed for all three QoIs across both laboratories. The model is judged credible for its intended use.",
